Nyamira Council of Elders on Friday endorsed PDP's Mwancha Okioma to run for governor.The elders said his track record speaks for itself and he has what it takes to lead the county to greater heights. Addressing the press at the council&rsquo;s regional office in Kisii, secretary Samuel Bosire Angwenyi said they held consultative meetings with various groups before arriving at the decision.&ldquo;Okioma is a visionary leader whose leadership can never be doubted by anybody because he has the relevant qualifications,&rdquo; he said. Okioma, who was present, thanked the elders for their endorsement and said he is prepared to serve the people if elected as the next governor.&ldquo;I want to assure them that I will serve all people with bias if elected,&rdquo; Okioma said.&ldquo;We have been holding consultative meetings with various groups, aspirants and opinion leaders in relation with the forthcoming elections and thus their contributions have given us the direction to take,&rdquo; They added Angwenyi said that they took into account the county&rsquo;s development, cohesion and inclusivity of the people of Nyamira in John Nyagarama&rsquo;s administration and thus arrived at a conclusion that he has been bias in service delivery.They said that Okioma is a visionary leader whose leadership can never be doubted by the residents.